The policies can use any type of attributes (user attributes, resource attributes, object, environment attributes etc.). Read more here - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attribute-based_access_control  ABAC Policy Language is used by ABAC to author policies. A policy consists of rules, which have "when" conditions and "then" actions. Policies are executed in a bounded time, goaled to reach a decision as quickly as possible in deterministic, fast and reliable way. Further light-weight execution consumes minimal resources.
